{"id":46698,"date":"2025-01-16T14:40:53","date_gmt":"2025-01-16T19:40:53","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/jamesclear.vercel.app\/?post_type=3-2-1&#038;p=46698"},"modified":"2025-01-16T14:40:53","modified_gmt":"2025-01-16T19:40:53","slug":"january-16-2025","status":"publish","type":"3-2-1","link":"https:\/\/jamesclear.vercel.app\/3-2-1\/january-16-2025","title":{"rendered":"3-2-1: On magic bullets, how to handle criticism, and what to let go of this year"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h2 id=\"h-3-ideas-from-me\">3 Ideas From Me<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>I.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;The source of healthy boundaries is self-love and self-respect. When you learn to love yourself, you are less likely to put up with people who don&#8217;t love you back.&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>(<\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/ctt.ac\/n62ee\">\u200b\u200b<em>Share this on X<\/em>\u200b\u200b<\/a><em>)<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200bII.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;Caring about everything is a disaster.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Caring about nothing is also a disaster.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Nurture the small pocket of things that truly matter to you.&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>(<\/em>\u200b<a href=\"https:\/\/ctt.ac\/v9i_q\">\u200b<em>Share this on X<\/em>\u200b\u200b<\/a><em>)<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p>III.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;People who rarely receive criticism often take feedback too personally and miss opportunities to learn.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>People who frequently receive criticism get used to ignoring what others say and also miss opportunities to learn.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The thing to focus on is the pattern. If you hear something once, don&#8217;t let it wreck your mindset. There are many ways to view the world and not everyone will agree with your approach.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>But if you&#8217;re hearing something repeatedly, think carefully about whether the feedback is right.&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>2 Quotes From Others<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>I.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Mathematician and NASA scientist <strong>Katherine Johnson<\/strong>, who played a key role in sending the first astronauts to space, on what it took to accomplish the mission:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;There were no textbooks, so we had to write them.&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Source: Interview on NASA website (2015)<\/em> <a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/3UopMzX\">\u200b\u200b\u200b<\/a><em><\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200bII.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Animal behavior scientist <strong>Temple Grandin <\/strong>on progress:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;People are always looking for the single magic bullet that will completely change everything. There is no single magic bullet. Progress is about bridging the gap between what we observe and what we can imagine \u2014 one careful step at a time.&#8221;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Source: <\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/3DUGdP4\">\u200b<em>Thinking in Pictures<\/em><\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>1 Question For You<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>What do I need to let go of this year to create space for what I really want?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>(\u200b<a href=\"https:\/\/ctt.ac\/cWhZa\">\u200b<em>Share this on X<\/em>\u200b<\/a>\u200b)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Until next week,<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>James Clear <a href=\"https:\/\/jamesclear.vercel.app\/atomic-habits\">\u200b\u200b\u200b<\/a> <br><em>Author of <\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/jamesclear.vercel.app\/atomic-habits\">\u200b<em>Atomic Habits<\/em>\u200b<\/a><em> <\/em><br><em>Creator of the <\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/jamesclear.vercel.app\/3-2-1\">\u200b<em>3-2-1 Newsletter<\/em>\u200b<\/a><em> <\/em><br><em>Founding Author of <\/em><a href=\"https:\/\/authorsequity.com\/\">\u200b<em>Authors Equity<\/em>\u200b<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:30px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>p.s. <a href=\"https:\/\/x.com\/bobvulfov\/status\/861808496098127873\">\u200b<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/jamesclear.vercel.app\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/01\/Screenshot-2025-01-16-at-2.31.33\u202fPM.png\">Thanks for asking<\/a>\u200b&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>3 Ideas From Me I. &#8220;The source of healthy boundaries is self-love and self-respect. When you learn to love yourself, you are less likely to put up with people who don&#8217;t love you back.&#8221; (\u200b\u200bShare this on X\u200b\u200b) \u200bII. &#8220;Caring about everything is a disaster. Caring about nothing is also a disaster. Nurture the small [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":40295,"menu_order":0,"template":"","acf":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO Premium plugin v20.5 (Yoast SEO v20.6) - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>3-2-1: On magic bullets, how to handle criticism, and what to let go of this year - James Clear<\/title>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/jamesclear.vercel.app\/3-2-1\/january-16-2025\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"3-2-1: On magic bullets, how to handle criticism, and what to let go of this year\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"3 Ideas From Me I. &#8220;The source of healthy boundaries is self-love and self-respect. When you learn to love yourself, you are less likely to put up with people who don&#8217;t love you back.&#8221; (\u200b\u200bShare this on X\u200b\u200b) \u200bII. &#8220;Caring about everything is a disaster. Caring about nothing is also a disaster. Nurture the small [&hellip;]\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https:\/\/jamesclear.vercel.app\/3-2-1\/january-16-2025\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"Ja